iner]] ran aground at Brook Point, [[Isle of Wight]], United Kingdom. Later refloated.<ref name=Times220754>{{Cite newspaper The Times |articlename=News in Brief |day_of_week=Thursday |date=22 July 1954 |page_number=2 |issue=52990 |column=G }}</ref> }}\n{{shipwreck list end}}\n\n===26 July===\n{{shipwreck list begin |date=26 July 1954 |sort=}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{MV|Traute Sarnow||2}} \n|flag={{Flag|West Germany}}\n|desc=The coaster ran aground on Gurnard's Head. All crew and the ship's dog saved.<ref name=Ives>{{cite web |title = 1946-62 |publisher = St. Ives Trust |url = http://www.stivestrust.co.uk/html/1946_-_1962.HTM |accessdate = 15 March 2008 |url-status = dead |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20080305055838/http://www.stivestrust.co.uk/html/1946_-_1962.HTM |archivedate = 5 March 2008 |df = dmy-all }}</ref><ref name=Sarnow>{{cite web |url=http://www.wrecksite.eu/wreck.aspx?76129 |title=MV Traute Sarnow (+1954) |publisher=Wrecksite |accessdate=21 September 2011}}</ref> }}\n{{shipwreck list end}}\n\n===27 July===\n{{shipwreck list begin |date=27 July 1954 |sort=}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{MV|Cressington Court||2}} \n|flag={{Flag|United Kingdom|civil}}\n|desc=The cargo ship collided with {{SS|Marinero||2}} ({{flag|Argentina}}) in the [[R\u00edo de la Plata|River Plate]], [[Buenos Aires]], Argentina.\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Navarino||2}} \n|flag={{flag|United Kingdom|civil}}\n|desc=The cargo ship ran aground in the River Plate, Buenos Aires, Argentina.<ref name=Times280754>{{Cite newspaper The Times |articlename=British Ships In Mishaps At Buenos Aires |day_of_week=Wednesday |date=28 July 1954 |page_number=8 |issue=52995 |column=D }}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Rippingham Grange||2}} \n|flag={{flag|United Kingdom|civil}}\n|desc=The cargo ship collided with {{SS|Mormacvale||2}} ({{flag|United States}}) in the River Plate, Buenos Aires, Argentina.<ref name=Times280754/> }}\n{{shipwreck list end}}\n\n===31 