tish Ships In Difficulties |day_of_week=Friday |date=8 October 1954 |page_number=8 |issue=53057 |column=D }}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Mormackite||2}} \n|flag={{flag|United States}}\n|desc=The ore carrier capsized and sank off [[Virginia]] with the loss of 37 of her 48 crew.<ref name=Times111054a>{{Cite newspaper The Times |articlename=American Ship Capsized |day_of_week=Monday |date=11 October 1954 |page_number=6 |issue=53059 |column=D }}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Rikke Skou||2}} \n|flag={{flag|Denmark}}\n|desc=The cargo ship sank off [[Terschelling]], Netherlands with the loss of twelve of her twenty crew.\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Seahorse||2}} \n|flag={{flag|United Kingdom|civil}}\n|desc=The coaster ran aground in the Scheldt, Belgium. Later refloated.<ref name=Times081054/> }}\n{{shipwreck list end}}\n\n===9 October===\n{{shipwreck list begin |date=9 October 1954 |sort=}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{MV|Emma Bakke|1929|2}} \n|flag={{flag|Norway}}\n|desc=The cargo ship was in the [[Atlantic Ocean]] when there was a boiler explosion and she was set on fire. The crew abandoned ship, and were rescued by {{SS|Corrientes||2}} ({{flag|Argentina}}). They were landed at [[Lisbon]], Portugal. Two crew were killed in the explosion and the ship sank.<ref name=Times111054b>{{Cite newspaper The Times |articlename=Norwegian Ship Sunk In Atlantic |day_of_week=Monday |date=11 October 1954 |page_number=6 |issue=53059 |column=D }}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Jane Stove||2}} \n|flag={{flag|Norway}}\n|desc=The cargo ship suffered a fracture to her main deck whilst in the [[North Sea]]. She reached the [[Faroe Islands]] on 10 October.<ref name=Times111054c>{{Cite newspaper The Times |articlename=Damaged Ship Reaches Faroes |day_of_week=Monday |date=11 October 1954 |page_number=6 |issue=53059 |column=D }}</ref> }}\n{{shipwreck list end}}\n\n===14 October===\n{{shipwreck list begin |date=14 October 1954 |sort=}}\n{