f>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list end}}\n\n===25 March===\n{{shipwreck list begin |date=25 March 1954 |sort=}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|Spanish minesweeper|Guadalete||2}}\n|flag={{flag|Spain|1938|name=Spanish Coast Guard}}\n|desc=The [[Minesweeper (ship)|minesweeper]] sank in storm off [[Gibraltar]].<ref>Gardiner, Robert, ed., ''Conway\u2032s All the World\u2032s Fighting Ships 1947\u20131982 Part I: The Western Powers,'' Annapolis, Maryland: Naval Institute Press, 1983, {{ISBN|0-87021-418-7}}, p. 110.</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list end}}\n\n===26 March===\n{{shipwreck list begin |date=26 March 1954 |sort=}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{Ship|SPS|DM-5 Guadalete||6}} \n|flag={{Navy|Spain}}\n|desc=The [[Minesweeper (ship)|minesweeper]] foundered in the Mediterranean Sea {{convert|20|nmi|km}} east of [[Gibraltar]] with the loss of 33 of her 77 crew. The survivors were rescued by {{SS|Potestas||2}} ({{flag|Italy|civil}}). {{HMS|Superb|25|6}} ({{navy|UK}}) assisted in the rescue operation.<ref name=Times260354>{{Cite newspaper The Times |articlename=Spanish Minesweeper Lost In Gale |day_of_week=Saturday |date=27 March 1954 |page_number=6 |issue=52891 |column=C }}</ref> }}\n{{shipwreck list end}}\n\n===30 March===\n{{shipwreck list begin |date=30 March 1954 |sort=}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{MV|Empire Windrush||2}} \n|flag={{Flag|United Kingdom|civil}}\n|desc=The [[ocean liner]] sank in the Mediterranean Sea following an explosion and fire in the engine room on 29 March. All passengers and crew rescued apart from the four killed in the explosion. }}\n{{shipwreck list end}}\n\n==April==\n\n===7 April===\n{{shipwreck list begin |date=7 April 1954 |sort=}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Francescu||2}} \n|flag={{flag|Italy|civil}}\n|desc=The cargo ship ran aground in the [[Scheldt]], Belgium and broke in two.<ref name=Times080454>{{Cite newspaper The Times |articlename=Italian Ship Breaks In Two |day_of_week=Thursday |date=8 April 1954 |page_number=5 |issue=52901 