otor]] [[cargo vessel]] was beached near [[Petersburg, Alaska|Petersburg]] in [[Southeast Alaska]] after striking a log, and became a [[total loss]].<ref name=alaskashipwreckss>[https://alaskashipwreck.com/shipwrecks-a-z/alaska-shipwrecks-s/ alaskashipwreck.com Alaska Shipwrecks (S)]</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list end}}\n\n===8 August===\n{{shipwreck list begin |date=8 August 1954 |sort=}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{MV|Spanker||2}} \n|flag={{flag|United Kingdom|civil}}\n|desc=The cargo ship ran aground at [[Hoek van Holland]], Netherlands and was holed.<ref name=Times090854>{{Cite newspaper The Times |articlename=British Ship Aground |day_of_week=Monday |date=9 August 1954 |page_number=5 |issue=53005 |column=E }}</ref> }}\n{{shipwreck list end}}\n\n===13 August===\n{{shipwreck list begin |date= 13 August 1954 |sort=}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship=''Sally''\n|flag={{flag|United States|1912}}\n|desc=The 10-[[gross register ton]], {{convert|33.2|ft|m|adj=on}} [[fishing vessel]] was destroyed by fire at [[Malina Bay]] ({{coord|58|13|N|153|05|W|name=Malina Bay}}) near [[Kodiak, Alaska|Kodiak]], [[Territory of Alaska]].<ref name=alaskashipwreckss>[https://alaskashipwreck.com/shipwrecks-a-z/alaska-shipwrecks-s/ alaskashipwreck.com Alaska Shipwrecks (S)]</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list end}}\n\n===19 August===\n{{shipwreck list begin |date=19 August 1954 |sort=}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{ship|ST|Applegarth||2}} \n|flag={{flag|United Kingdom|civil}}\n|desc=The tug sank at Canning Dock, [[Liverpool]], [[Lancashire]].<ref name=Times200854>{{Cite newspaper The Times |articlename=News in Brief |day_of_week=Friday |date=20 August 1954 |page_number=3 |issue=53015 |column=G }}</ref> }}\n{{shipwreck list end}}\n\n===27 August===\n{{shipwreck list begin |date= 27 August 1954 |sort=}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship=''Lawrence P''\n|flag={{flag|United States|1959}}\n|desc=The 22-[[gross register ton]], {{convert|42|ft|m|1|adj=on}} [[fishing vessel]] foundered {{convert|65|nmi}} west of [[Yakutat, Alaska|Yakutat]], [[Territory of Alaska]].<ref name=alaskashipwrecksl>[https://alaskashipwreck.com/shipwrecks-a-z/alaska-shipwrecks-l/ alaskashipwreck.com Alaska Shipwrecks (L)]</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list end}}\n\n===28 August===\n{{shipwreck list begin |date=28 August 1954 |sort=}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{MV|Prince de Liege||2}} \n|flag={{Flag|Belgium}}\n|desc=The cargo ship ran aground in the [[Niger Delta]], [[Nigeria]]. Refloated 13 October 1954 with assistance from [[tugboat|tug]] ''Poolzee'' ({{flag|Netherlands}}).<ref name=BelgePZ>{{cite web|url=http://www.belgischekoopvaardij.net/belgian%20Merchant%20%20P-Z.pdf |title=Belgian Merchant P-Z |publisher=Belgische Koopvaardij |accessdate=1 December 2010 }}{{dead link|date=May 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> }}\n{{shipwreck list end}}\n\n===29 August===\n{{shipwreck list begin |date=29 August 1954 |sort=}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Donalourdes||2}} \n|flag={{flag|Philippines}}\n|desc=The cargo ship was driven ashore at [[Kowloon]], Hong Kong in a typhoon.<ref name=Times300854b>{{Cite newspaper The Times |articlename=Formosa Hit By Typhoon |day_of_week=Monday |date=30 August 1954 |page_number=5 |issue=52023 |column=B }}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Northern Princess||2}} \n|flag={{flag|Panama}}\n|desc=The cargo ship was driven ashore at Kowloon, Hong Kong in a typhoon.<ref name=Times300854b/>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Orelia||2}} \n|flag={{flag|United Kingdom|civil}}\n|desc=The [[ore carrier]] ran aground at [[Port Talbot]], [[Glamorgan]]. Later refloated.<ref name=Times300854a>{{Cite newspaper The Times |articlename=Ore Ship Refloated |day_of_week=Monday |date=30 August 1954 |page_number=3 |issue=52023 |column=B }}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Thorncombe||2}} \n|flag={{flag|United Kingdom|civil}}\n|desc=The cargo ship was driven ashore at Kowloon, Hong Kong in a typhoon.<ref name=Times300854b/> }}\n{{shipwreck 