iewtopic.php?f=149&t=50411 |title=Chinese Naval Battles (Civil War and later)|accessdate=21 February 2019}}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list end}}\n\n===21 September===\n{{shipwreck list begin |date=21 September 1954 |sort=}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship=''Avona'' \n|flag={{flag|United States|1912}}\n|desc=The 15-[[gross register ton]], {{convert|36.7|ft|m|1|adj=on}} [[fishing vessel]] sank northwest of [[Hive Island]] ({{coord|59|53|N|149|22|W|name=Hive Island}}) at the entrance to [[Resurrection Bay]] on the [[Southcentral Alaska|south-central]] coast of the [[Territory of Alaska]].<ref name=alaskashipwrecksa>[https://alaskashipwreck.com/shipwrecks-a-z/alaska-shipwrecks-a/ alaskashipwreck.com Alaska Shipwrecks (A)]</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list end}}\n\n===22 September===\n{{shipwreck list begin |date=22 September 1954 |sort=}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Nordstjernen|1937|2}} \n|flag={{flag|Norway}}\n|desc=The [[passenger ship]] struck a rock and sank off the [[Lofoten Islands]] with the loss of three lives. Over 200 passengers and crew were rescued.<ref name=Times230954>{{Cite newspaper The Times |articlename=200 Rescued After Shipwreck |day_of_week=Thursday |date=23 September 1954 |page_number=6 |issue=53044 |column=C }}</ref>\n}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship={{SS|Semiramis||2}} \n|flag={{flag|Greece}}\n|desc=The passenger ship ran aground at [[Brindisi]], Italy.<ref name=Times240954>{{Cite newspaper The Times |articlename=News in Brief |day_of_week=Friday |date=24 September 1954 |page_number=7 |issue=53045 |column=G }}</ref> }}\n{{shipwreck list end}}\n\n===25 September===\n{{shipwreck list begin |date= 25 September 1954 |sort=}}\n{{shipwreck list item\n|ship=''Oregon Wolf''\n|flag={{flag|United States|1960}}\n|desc=The 48-[[gross register ton]], {{convert|58.6|ft|m|1|adj=on}} [[motor vessel]] sank in [[Frederick Sound]] in the [[Alexander Archipelago]] in [[Southeast Alaska]] approximately {{convert|3|nmi}} east of [[Turnabout Island (Alaska)|Turnabout Isla